 - 1 Dumbarton, Wednesday, August 26th 1953 |publisher=The Sons Archive |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|team1 =[[Dunfermline Athletic F.C.|Dunfermline Athletic]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Smith {{goal|6}}<br>Currie {{goal|22}}{{goal|}}<br>Henderson {{goal|46}}<br>O'Brien {{goal||pen}}<br>Mailer {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =Irwin {{goal||pen}}\n|stadium=[[East End Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =H Phiilips\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =29 August 1953\n|round =[[1953\u201354 Scottish League Cup#Group 8|Section 8]]\n|score = 4\u20130<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.fitbastats.com/dumbarton/game.php?gameid=36760 |title=Arbroath 4 - 0 Dumbarton, League Cup (29/08/1953)|publisher=Fitbastats.com |accessdate=15 April 2020}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sonsarchive.com/matchdetails.php?id=1721 |title=Arbroath 4 - 0 Dumbarton, Saturday, August 29th 1953 |publisher=The Sons Archive |accessdate=12 April 2020}}</ref>\n|team1 =[[Arbroath F.C.|Arbroath]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Malcolm {{goal|}}{{goal|}}<br>McKenzie {{goal|}}<br>McCall {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =\n|stadium=[[Gayfield Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =J Barclay\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==[[Stirlingshire Cup]]==\nDumbarton's disastrous season was completed as their grip on the Stirlingshire Cup was easily released by defeat in the first round to Falkirk.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =7 September 1953\n|round =First Round\n|score = 5\u20130\n|team1 =[[Falkirk F.C.|Falkirk]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =Dunlop {{goal|}}{{goal|}}<br>McCrae {{goal|}}<br>Bell,J {{goal||OG}}<br>Barclay {{goal|}}\n|goals2 = \n|stadium=[[Brockville Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Dewar Shield==\nThe Dewar Shield was a competition played between the previous season's champions of Aberdeenshire, Forfarshire, Perthshire and Stirlingshire. Dumbarton were drawn to meet the Aberdeenshire Cup holders, Buckie Thistle, but no doubt due to travel costs, Dumbarton withdrew.\n\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = L\n|date =\n|round =Semi Final\n|score = [[Walkover|WO]]\n|team1 =[[Buckie Thistle F.C.|Buckie Thistle]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 =\n|goals2 = \n|stadium=\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Friendlies==\nDespite being two of the oldest clubs in Scotland, Dumbarton and Stranraer's first XIs met for the first time in two friendly matches.\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = D\n|date =27 February 1954\n|round =[[Friendly Match|Friendly]]\n|score = 2\u20132\n|team1 =[[Stranraer F.C.|Stranraer]]\n|team2 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|goals1 = {{goal|}}<br> {{goal|}}\n|goals2 =Bell,T {{goal|}}<br>McCaffrey {{goal|}} \n|stadium=[[Stair Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n{{football box collapsible\n|result  = W\n|date =24 April 1954\n|round =[[Friendly Match|Friendly]]\n|score = 3\u20130\n|team1 =[[Dumbarton F.C.|Dumbarton]]\n|team2 =[[Stranraer F.C.|Stranraer]]\n|goals1 = {{goal|}}<br> {{goal|}}<br> {{goal|}}\n|goals2 = \n|stadium=[[Boghead Park]]\n|attendance =\n|referee =\n|motm =\n}}\n\n==Player statistics==\n{{Efs start|[[1953\u201354 Scottish Division Two|B Division]]|[[1953\u201354 Scottish Cup|Scottish Cup]]|[[1953\u201354 Scottish League Cup|League Cup]]}}\n{{Efs player|name=Wallace Murdoch<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=125 |title=Wallace Murdoch - Player Statistics |publisher=The Sons Archive |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>|pos=GK|nat=SCO|17|0|0|0|6|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[Walter Scott (footballer, born 1932)|Walter Scott]]|pos=GK|nat=SCO|13|0|1|0|0|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=Danny Bell<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sonsarchive.com/player.php?id=188 |title=Danny Bell - Player Statistics |publisher=The Sons Archive |accessdate=14 April 2020}}</ref>|pos=DF|nat=SCO|17|0|1|0|6|0}}\n{{Efs player|name=[[George Ferguson (footballer)|George Ferguson]]<ref>The league match against St Johnstone on 27 March